      "Failed UPS-7560 identified and locked out",
      "UPS-7560 placed in bypass and taken out of service",
      "Spare circuit activated to provide power to quarters"
    ],
    "summary": "On January 3, 2023, at 2210 hours, a DC capacitor on Universal Power Supply UPS-7560 failed at the Perdido Spar platform, causing smoke release, arcing/sparking, and activation of smoke detectors. The automated safety system shut-in the facility and caused full power loss. The Fire Team responded but found no visible fire. The Electrical Team isolated power feeds and identified the failed inverter through troubleshooting. The UPS was locked out and bypassed, with a spare circuit providing power. Estimated repair cost is $56,830 with 7-9 weeks lead time for parts. No injuries or pollution occurred.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Implement Preventative Maintenance Plan (PMI) to replace all fans, AC and DC capacitors on like units"
    ],
